Recommended Roadmap
1. Finish Backend Properly ✅ (Current Phase)

Before K8s/DevOps, make sure backend is production-ready.

Focus on:

Authentication (JWT)
CRUD APIs
Validation
Error handling
Logging
Database migrations (Alembic)
Environment configs
API testing
Docker working perfectly

You are here right now.

2. Build Frontend 🎨

YES — now you should start frontend.

Because:

You need a full-stack app before deployment.
CI/CD makes more sense when frontend + backend both exist.
Kubernetes is mainly useful when deploying complete services.

Recommended stack:

Frontend Stack
React + Vite
TailwindCSS
Axios
React Router
Context API / Redux Toolkit
3. Connect Frontend ↔ Backend

This is very important.

You’ll learn:

CORS
API calls
Authentication flow
Token storage
Protected routes
State management
4. Dockerize Frontend Too 🐳

Then your project becomes:

Frontend Container
Backend Container
PostgreSQL Container

At this point:

Use:

docker-compose

This is VERY important before Kubernetes.

5. Learn Docker Compose

This is the real next step after frontend.

You’ll create:

services:
  frontend:
  backend:
  postgres:

Then run entire app with:

docker-compose up

Industry-style local development starts here.

6. THEN Move to CI/CD 🚀

After full app works:

Learn:

GitHub Actions
Auto testing
Auto Docker build
Push images to DockerHub

Example flow:

Push code → GitHub Actions runs → Docker image builds → Deploy
7. THEN Kubernetes ☸️

Kubernetes before finishing frontend/full-stack is overkill.

K8s makes sense when you already have:

Multiple containers
Scaling
CI/CD
Production deployment

Then learn:

Pods
Deployments
Services
Ingress
ConfigMaps
Secrets
Helm
Monitoring
Best Order For You
Backend APIs
→ Frontend
→ Frontend + Backend Integration
→ Docker Compose
→ CI/CD
→ Kubernetes